pr_title: feat: add Sidebar, LocalDomain in GCBM. WIP.
pr_body:
## Description
Added a Sidebar for the top-level configs in GCBM. Added a LocalDomain component. Still a WIP.

## Testing
Click on Explore in the GCBM card on the landing page.

## Additional Context (Please include any Screenshots/gifs if relevant)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35102959/174278950-d5334c9c-ccdf-4f0f-9249-8725f1e8552a.png)
Nothing is working yet, I'll work on adding sub-menus in each config as I progress through them in the upcoming weeks. 
The `/gcbm/configurations` page will give an overview of the simulation, and the configs will have their separate paths. 
For eg.: `gcbm/configurations/local-domain` for the Local Domain config.

- Adds the Pools config in GCBM Simulation Editor.

pr_title: feat: add UI for Spinup, Run simulation, DB Editor, Integrate upload endpoints
pr_body:
## Description
- Adds UI for Spinup config & run simulation section
- Integrated backend upload endpoints
- Adds a button for editing column names in DB editor, and show edited cells in a different color. 

## Testing
1. Go to `/gcbm/configurations/spinup-parameters` and `/gcbm/run` for the UI changes
2. Go to /gcbm/upload/input-db and upload a DB file (the proper JSON response with table, column names is not yet added in the backend) and click on edit button to change column names.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35102959/181914182-67fe1766-b228-403d-bbe2-f4f780ec8712.mp4




## Additional Context (Please include any Screenshots/gifs if relevant)
WIP.

pr_title: feat: add UI for Import Simulation modal, connect LocalDomain to the vuex store
pr_body:
## Description
- Adds Import Simulation modal in the sidebar (users can upload all the files required by the simulation. If config files are provided, they will be read and the UI will be updated accordingly. If not, the default configs will be used)
- Connects LocalDomain with the vuex store.
- Integrates tables endpoint in input db for fetching attribute names.
- Adds UI for changing table names

## Testing
Go to /gcbm and click on "Import" in the sidebar.
